# Wilma Communication Channel

**WILMA-BAMBAM.md** (repo root) is the task and message channel from Wilma (24/7 assistant) to Bam-Bam (you).

**When you start a session:**
- Open **WILMA-BAMBAM.md** and scan the **Active Items** section for pending tasks.
- Work on items as appropriate.
- Post responses/updates in the **Log** section with timestamps (add a row: When | Who | Message).
- If you need clarification from Wilma, ask in the Log (or in Active Items) and note that you're waiting for her response.

**During the session:**
- Periodically re-check **WILMA-BAMBAM.md** (e.g. every 15 minutes or when switching context) for new Active Items.
- Same workflow: work, log, ask if blocked.

**When you complete work:**
- Move the item from **Active Items** to **Completed**.
- Add a Log entry noting what was done.

This is async communication — Wilma posts tasks; you respond in this file.
